        -:  657:// Floating point, integer, and Number values encode as JSON numbers.
        -:  658://
        -:  659:// String values encode as Hjson strings (quoteless, multiline or
        -:  660:// JSON).
        -:  661://
        -:  662:// Array and slice values encode as JSON arrays.
        -:  663://
        -:  664:// Map values encode as JSON objects. The map's key type must be a
        -:  665:// string. The map keys are used as JSON object keys.
        -:  666://
        -:  667:// JSON cannot represent cyclic data structures and Marshal does not
        -:  668:// handle them. Passing cyclic structures to Marshal will result in
